The '''''Journal of Competition Law & Economics''''' (print: {{ISSN|1744-6414}}, online: {{ISSN|1744-6422}}) is a quarterly [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[law journal]] dedicated to competition [[law and economics]], published by [[Oxford University Press]]. The journal was established in March 2004. The first issue was published in March 2005. The [[Editor in chief|editors]] are [[J. Gregory Sidak]] ([[Criterion Economics]]),<ref>Criterion Economics L.L.C., http://www.criterioneconomics.com (last visited Sept. 17, 2013).</ref> and Damien Geradin ([[Covington & Burling]]).<ref>Covington & Burling LLP, Damien Geradin, http://www.cov.com/dgeradin/ (last visited Sept. 17, 2013).</ref>

